subtitle: Hello, I'm Jeffrey Mishlove. You know, a
few weeks ago I made a promise that I
was going to endeavour to get better at
karaoke. I was going to share that
with you, hopefully as an inspiration for
you to get better at whatever you choose.
So, I've selected a whole new set of
songs. I moved the karaoke machine
right here into the recording studio to
get better lighting and better sound.
I think… I've been practicing, I've been
rehearsing, I think I'm at least a little
bit better now. What do you think?
Here are some songs. I hope you enjoy
them.
[Music “Summertime,” the Ella Fitzegerald version]
[Music “Sunny Afternoon” by The Kinks]
This song has a bit of a special meaning
for me because in 1967 when Otis
Redding's
airplane crashed into Lake Winona next
to Madison, Wisconsin, I was living in
Madison at the time, so his death had an
impact on me.
[Music “The Dock of the Bay” by Otis Redding]
[Music “Boondocks” by Little Big Town]
